# Development Rules & Framework Architecture

## Core Philosophy
- **Alphire** is the company; **StarCaster** is the product. Repository: `~/WebApps/starcaster`.
- Target users: influencers, content creators, communities, and grassroots builders who grow organic followings through comment-section and social engagement (likes, shares, replies) across articles, posts, tweets, videos, and the wider social web.
- Prioritize vanilla, highly decoupled architectures. Keep modules small and predictable.
- **Craftsman mindset:** take time to build well; discover before coding; plan non-trivial work; surgical edits on large files (`develop.js`, `messaging.js`, `devAgent.js`, generated `index.html`).
- **Normie** (`~/WebApps/normie`) is the primary reference/test project for fleshing out StarCaster flows.
- Avoid unnecessary dependencies; use native web standards where possible.
- Maintain clean, atomic git commits. Do not add placeholder/TODO comments unless asked.

## Conversation scope (thread hygiene)

The operator often shifts between tasks in one session. **Watch for tangents** and suggest a **new Cursor chat thread** when the work is a different deliverable — do not wait to be asked.

### When to suggest a new thread

- A **different deliverable** (e.g. auth landing → X OAuth → Supabase migration).
- The current task is **done** or blocked, and what’s next is unrelated.
- **Many failed iterations** on one problem; a clean thread + clear spec would help.
- Phrases like “while we’re here,” “also,” or “one more thing” about another module, page, or system.

### Stay in the same thread

- **Direct follow-ups** on the same deliverable (copy tweak, spacing, bug in code just written).
- A **small dependency** of the current task (e.g. legal URLs needed for auth already in progress).

### Handoff protocol (when suggesting a switch)

1. **Say so briefly** — what’s wrapped up vs what the tangent is; offer to finish the current slice first if mid-edit.
2. **Operator** starts the new thread and gives it a **clear title** (matches the new topic).
3. **Agent (this thread)** writes a handoff markdown file before the switch:
   - Path: `docs/Cursor Threads/<Thread Title>.md` (use a short, descriptive title; sanitize filename).
   - Contents: goal, what was completed, what’s open, key files, success criteria, paste-ready prompt for the new thread, links to mockups/specs mentioned in chat.
   - Model after `docs/Cursor Threads/Cursor Recommendations 1-3.md`.
4. **Operator** opens the new thread, attaches or references that handoff file, and continues there.

Do **not** start unrelated work in the current thread just because context is already loaded.

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend:** Vanilla JS SPA (`public/js/*` on `window.App`), HTML partials (`src/pages/` → `build:html`), CSS in `src/css/` (bundled to `public/styles.css`). **No Tailwind.** No component library.
- **React:** Only the Campaigns list island (`react-entry.js` → `public/bundle.js`). Default new UI to vanilla unless explicitly directed otherwise.
- **Backend:** Node.js; shared dispatcher `routes/index.js` (local `server.js` + Vercel `api/[...slug].js`).
- **Database:** Supabase (PostgreSQL). SQL setup files in `docs/`. No migration runner — apply SQL manually and track per environment.
- **Hosting:** Vercel. Production filesystem is read-only — no `data/*.json` writes in prod.
- **Rich text (where used):** Tiptap packages in `package.json` — pin versions; do not upgrade casually.

## Style Guide (Compiled UI Standards)

Sourced from `docs/UI_STANDARDS.md`, `docs/STYLE_GUIDE.md`, and prior agent/human sessions. Full CSS blueprints live in `src/css/` — especially `_tables.css`, `_forms.css`, `_buttons.css`.

### Development workflow (UI-related)
- **Zero hacky edits:** no broad regex replacements across monolith files; use precise, line-targeted changes.
- **Mandatory discovery:** grep/trace DOM IDs and `App.*` handlers before changing markup or handlers.
- **Planning:** non-trivial UI → brief implementation plan before code.
- **Surgical precision:** edit `src/pages/*.html` + run `npm run build:html`; do not casually rewrite all of `public/index.html`.

### Buttons & actions
- Never style bare `button` / `input` globally for layout; use utility classes:
  - Primary: `btn btn-primary`
  - Secondary/ghost: `btn btn-ghost`
  - Destructive: `btn btn-danger`
  - Table micro-actions: `btn tiny-btn icon-btn`
- **Button labels:** Title Case (`Save Settings`, `Add Contact`, not sentence case).
- **Button text must not wrap:** use `white-space: nowrap`; size with `width: fit-content` + horizontal padding — not full width unless layout requires it.
- **Icon-only buttons:** square container (e.g. 28×28px), `inline-flex` centered; no text inside; use `aria-label` (Title Case, e.g. `Delete`, `Save`). In `.standard-form-grid`, set explicit width/height and `min-width: 0` (may need `!important` if parent forces 100% width).

### Typography & page chrome
- Headings `h1`–`h6` and `p` use locked line-heights in bundled CSS; body text on white uses `var(--ink-primary)` / `var(--ink)` for contrast.
- **Page titles:** `<h2>` in `.page-heading-row` must use **`Module: Subpage`** format — e.g. `Contacts: Personnel`, `Acquire: Web`, `Builder: Forms`. Single colon + space. Not bare titles like `Manage Personas`.
- **Instructional text purge:** no paragraph summaries under `.page-heading-row` on hub pages; use structure, labels, and tooltips — not page-level bloat.

### CRUD data tables
- Canonical styles: `src/css/_tables.css`. **Do not create per-module header classes** (no `.contacts-actions-heading`, etc.).
- **Column headers:** plain `<th>` only — **never** put `<button>` or `<a>` inside `<th>`. Put sort `id` on the `<th>`; JS toggles sort and appends `▲`/`▼` to `textContent`.
- Header style: black `#000` background, white bold text, left-aligned; hover `#b8e0ff` / `#0b3d7a`; cursor pointer on sortable columns.
- **Actions column:** last column; `text-align: center` on header; use `.actions-col` on both `<th>` and `<td>`.
- **Action icons row:** treat edit/clone/delete (and similar) icons as one **monolithic row that never wraps**. Wrap buttons in `<div class="table-actions-row">` via `App.finishTableActionsCell(td, ...buttons)` (see `App.appendTableActions` in `public/js/core.js`). Canonical CSS: `src/css/_tables.css` (`.table-actions-row { display: inline-flex; flex-wrap: nowrap; }`). Do not stack action icons vertically or allow them to break across lines—use horizontal scroll on `.table-wrap` if the viewport is narrow.
- **Filter row:** `.table-filter-row` above header row; light background (`var(--bg-page)`), not black.
- **Sorting:** every data table must support column sort on string/date headers with `sortColumn` / `sortDirection` state.
- **Boolean filters:** use a single checkbox (e.g. `Has YouTube`) — not free-text URL fields for yes/no metadata.
- Wrap tables in `.table-wrap` for horizontal scroll on small viewports only — **not** inside form modals (see Modals).

### Forms & labels
- **Standard grid:** `.standard-form-grid` — `grid-template-columns: 140px 1fr`; labels in column 1 (not wrapping inputs), controls in column 2.
- **No placeholders for instructions:** fields blank by default; permanent `<label>` to the left (or above in `.form-group` stacks).
- **Content pickers (searchable combobox):** For dropdowns bound to long messaging/asset lists (campaign Content section, similar forms), use a **searchable combobox** — not a native `<select>` users must scroll. Pattern: hidden native `<select class="campaign-combobox-native">` (form value + `name`), visible `<input type="text">` for typing/filter, and `.campaign-combobox-list` listbox. IDs: `campaignFooSelect` → `campaignFooSearch` / `campaignFooListbox`. Populate via `setCampaignContentComboboxOptions()` in `public/js/campaigns.js`; wire once with `initCampaignContentComboboxes()`. Each option needs `value`, `label` (truncated display), and `searchText` (full text to match). **Hashtag multi-picker modal** (`openCampaignHashtagPicker`): search in modal header via `Modal` `headerTools`; filter checkbox grid as user types; **Save Hashtag** creates via `POST /api/messaging/hashtags` and selects for the campaign. Mechanics/short lists (channel, segment) may stay native `<select>`.
- **Vertical stacks in modals:** `.form-group` for label → input sequences.
- **Dense modals:** `.standard-form-grid-4col` when needed.
- **Checkboxes in grid:** `.standard-form-checkbox` on the input; group related checkboxes in a flex/grid in column 2 under one label.
- **Submit row:** empty `<div></div>` first cell, button in second column — or `.standard-form-grid-full` for full-width actions.
- **Validation glow:** persisted populated fields get green completeness outline; empty required fields red (existing pattern in app).

### Hero & collapsible inputs
- Primary focal inputs (e.g. Acquire URL bar): `.hero-action-input` — blue focus ring/glow without layout shift (`box-shadow` inset trick).

### Details / accordion
- Native `<details>` advanced blocks: `.hanging-details` on `<details>` so disclosure triangle hangs in left margin and title aligns flush with content.
- App collapsibles: `.accordion-header` button with `.accordion-title`, `.accordion-toggle`, `.accordion-arrow`; toggle **`aria-expanded` only** — do not rewrite button `innerHTML` for chevrons.

### Pods (hub / settings navigation)
- Hub pages: `.section-settings-shell` grid; each tile `.pod` with `.pod-icon-col` (left) + `.pod-content` (right).
- Icons: Lucide-style SVG ~84×84px, `stroke-width: 1px`, `color: var(--accent)` — no large inline flex style blobs on pods.

### Modals
- **Law: no scrollbars in form modals**, especially horizontal. Widen modal to fit tables; do not `overflow-x: auto` inside modal forms.

### Feedback & notices
- **Global status bar:** `App.notify(text, isError)` → `#message` (sticky bottom). Success-ish: `#fcebc8`; error: `#f7c6c6`.
- **Toasts (preferred for transient feedback):** `App.components.Toast` — `.c-toast`, variants `--success`, `--error`, `--info` (see `public/js/components.js`).
- **Auth messages:** `.auth-message` / `.auth-message.error` on login/register forms.
- **Inline save status (Builder):** `.develop-save-notice` / `.is-success` where used.

### CSS conventions
- Edit source in `src/css/`; run build so `public/styles.css` updates (`npm run build` or `npm run dev`).
- Use CSS variables from `src/css/_variables.css` (`--ink-primary`, `--border-light`, `--btn-bg`, etc.).
- Legacy rules live in `src/css/legacy.css` — prefer extending shared partials over duplicating.
- Avoid `!important` except icon buttons in grids and third-party overrides.

